For this task, create a VPC named devops-vpc in the us-east-1 region with the Amazon-provided IPv6 CIDR block using terraform.

The Terraform working directory is /home/bob/terraform. Create the main.tf file (do not create a different .tf file) to accomplish this task.

Solutions:- 

âœ… Terraform Configuration to Create a VPC with IPv6
. Create the main.tf file:

resource "aws_vpc" "devops_vpc" {
  cidr_block = "10.0.0.0/16"
  tags = {
    Name = "devops_vpc"
  }
  enable_dns_support = true
  enable_dns_hostnames = true

  assign_generated_ipv6_cidr_block = true
}

 Steps to Use This Terraform Code
Save the code in a file, e.g., main.tf.
Run the following commands:

terraform init
terraform plan
terraform apply
